<br>
Doing rods, and refreshing them takes very little space in a raid (just need a quite corner where you can move a few feet to move your pile of rods back and forth to refresh them) BUT it takes all of your time and attention, the mage gets no downtime while topping up the rods and refreshing the ones already there.  And the worst bit of all (at least for me) considering how much effort you are expending, is how little of the raid you actually get to see (gee, what a pretty floor, what zone were we in again?).<br>
<br>
Acting like you are working non-stop on the equivalent of power levelling a trade-skill for 3 or 4 hours straight or even longer, without a break, and without doing much else on the raid isn't exactly most people's idea of fun.  It definitely isn't mine anyway.  Yes we are needed, and there is a lot of satisfaction in knowing we probably made the whole raid possible (as much as anyone anyway), but it sure would be nice if we could enjoy it as well.  Face it, picking up 20 or 30 or more rods from one pile to move them to a new pile every 2 mins gets old really fast.<br>
<br>
I really hope one of the developers from Verant takes notice of this thread.  Giving rods a 15 minute decay timer, or even longer, would make being a raiding mage far far far more fun.  Maybe we could even look up from the floor every now and then and see what everyone else is doing?<br>
<br>
And for those of you who think the &quot;fill your inventory slots with something&quot; method of dropping rods is lame, try dropping your rods on the ground when you have half a dozen people or more standing on top of you in a busy area.  In those situations, there is no where to click to drop the rod safely 100% of the time without sometimes accidentally initiating a trade with another player or an NPC.  A drop button or drop area would be a very useful thing IMHO for dropping and refreshing rods...<br>
