Uhm Not sure about the rest of the Magicians out there but the mages in my guild do more damage then any other person at the raid, PERIOD!<br>
<br>
Who do you think made that rod the wizards are using to manaburn with at end?  Who do you think made that rod the druids are using to nuke with near the middle, and who do you think made those rods the clerics are using to keep the tank alive so everyone else can nuke/swing/debuff and gereally kill the mob?   WE MAGICIANS MADE THEM!<br>
<br>
We make or break the end encounters all the time. Sure if we have no tanks we might not win, but We've won when we ran out of tanks before and a SK stepped up to finish it off.  We make rods and coh during raids. Get over it that is what we've been called to do and we do it so that the raid as a WHOLE wins.<br>
<br>
Do NOT get me wrong. I am not overly joyed at making rods for a living.  I don't like having to make rods for a living.  But ya know what? IT IS a living and now I am required and even sought after for raids and it feels good for a change. <br>
<br>
NON-Lore Rods would be nice but doubtful they'd ever happen. Let's face it you have a force of 60 at a raid. Say 3 mages(average).  They make 10 slot bags and make sure that everyone comes to the raid with one empty slot to hold a bag.  Now those 60 people have a bag of 10 rods. That's 600 rods for the raid, not counting the ones mages make during raid because, as we all know, melee are stupid and without someone constantly bashing them over the head to do so they'll forget to drop their rods.  <br>
<br>
Drop command. erm i guess be nice kinda maybe sortta. I just hit key one and then drop the rod on my autoequip window and tada falls to ground.  I'd REALLY rather see a small window for autoequip only that is NOT buggy when used.<br>
<br>
I do not bother refreshing rods either. What I do is start summoning rods. Make a line of them then go back to begining and use the first few rods in the line myself to get back to full mana then start over again. this  ensures only the newest rods are on the ground and it is faster for me to grab 3 rods from the ground and get back 7 rods of mana then to cast rod, use rod, cast and so on.<br>
<br>
Oh well this is a dead horse we beating. Rods are here to stay and until you get your guildmates to stop being dum and realize you know wtf you are doing and to stop hollaring for rods for yardtrash and other useless times you'll continue to feel used and abused.<br>
